  "description": "<p>A serious jacket that knows how to have fun. The 3-layer eco-friendly Taslan fabric is highly water resistant and breathable to keep you dry and comfortable even when conditions have taken a turn. Ski-specific features include a helmet compatible hood and high pockets that are harness and backpack friendly. The underarm vents, articulated fit, and powder skirt set you up for surfing deep backcountry bowls and churning up steep approaches.</p><ul><li>Durable Taslan 3L nylon fabric is highly water-resistant, breathable, and eco-friendly</li><li>Fully seam-taped construction keeps you dry in howling conditions</li><li>Helmet-compatible hood has embedded cordlock adjustments for a snag-free profile</li><li>Articulated arms and patterning ensure unrestricted movement</li><li>Large front pockets sit high for backpack and harness compatibility</li><li>Underarm vents have 2-way zippers to release heat</li><li>Gripped snow skirt with snap closure keeps snow on the outside</li><li>Shock-cord adjustable hem seals out snow and drafts</li><li>Contoured cuffs layer well with gloves and close with Velcro\u00ae tabs</li><li>Built-in Recco\u00ae Rescue System reflector allows ski patrol and mountain rescue teams to detect and locate it under snow</li><li>Pairs perfectly with the Helix Pants or Helix Bib Pants for a backcountry-ready system</li></ul>",
